{"type":"message","id":"0ff061b2","parentId":"226a14d3","timestamp":"2026-03-26T02:45:26.671Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We attempted to navigate to a Brave profile that doesn't exist. Available profiles are \"openclaw\" and \"user\". We need to open Brave using an available profile. Likely the default is \"user\" for the logged-in user's Chromium. However, we may need to use the \"user\" profile to open a normal browser window.\n\nGiven the error: \"BrowserProfileNotFoundError: Profile \"brave\" not found. Available profiles: openclaw, user\". So we can use \"user\" profile to open the normal user profile.\n\nThus we need to call browser.navigate with target host (or default target?), profile \"user\", url \"https://www.youtube.com\". The browser action \"navigate\" can accept parameters: action: \"navigate\", target: \"host\" or \"node\"? Let's see tool definition:\n\n```\ntype browser = (_: {\n  // Control the browser via OpenClaw's browser control server (status/start/stop/profiles/tabs/open/snapshot/screenshot/actions). Browser choice: omit profile by default for the isolated OpenClaw-managed browser (`openclaw`). For the logged-in user browser on the local host, use profile=\"user\". A supported Chromium-based browser (v144+) must be running. Use only when existing logins/cookies matter and the user is present. When a node-hosted browser proxy is available, the tool may auto-route to it. Pin a node with node=<id|name> or target=\"node\". When using refs from snapshot (e.g. e12), keep the same tab: prefer passing targetId from the snapshot response into subsequent actions (act/click/type/etc). For stable, self-resolving refs across calls, use snapshot with refs=\"aria\" (Playwright aria-ref ids). Default refs=\"role\" are role+name-based. Use snapshot+act for UI automation. Avoid act:wait by default; use only in exceptional cases when no reliable UI state exists. target selects browser location (sandbox|host|node). 