\"start\" action signature likely uses \"target\"? Let's examine. The tool's arguments include many fields common to all actions, like \"action\", \"target\", \"profile\" etc. So we can call:\n\n{\n  \"action\": \"start\",\n  \"profile\": \"user\",\n  \"target\": \"host\"\n}\n\nBut is target required? Not sure. The spec: \"target\": might be required sometimes. Let's look at earlier calls: we used \"browser\" with target \"host\" and \"profile\": \"brave\", action: \"navigate\", url: \"https://www.youtube.com\". That gave error that profile not found. Also we tried \"profile\":\"user\", target:\"host\", action:\"navigate\", url: youtube.com, got timed out. So perhaps we need to start it first.\n\nThus we call browser with action \"start\", maybe we need to include \"profile\". Let's try:\n\n{\n  \"action\": \"start\",\n  \"profile\": \"user\",\n  \"target\": \"host\"\n}\n\nBut do we need additional fields? Maybe \"node\"? Not necessary. Let's try.\n\nAfter starting, we might need a short delay before navigating. Use \"navigate\" after a short yield.\n\nBut we need to handle this properly: it's a synchronous tool call pattern: we call start, then we might have to wait for it to be ready, but OpenClaw may already start it. The tool will respond with some result. Then we can call navigate.\n\nLet's attempt to start. Then we can navigate.\n\nThus, next step: call browser with action \"start\".\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_95a1155a5f0a467f96cc0bdf","name":"browser","arguments":{"target":"host","profile":"user","action":"start"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-nano-30b-a3b:free","usage":{"input":21995,"output":2531,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":24526,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774493153289,"responseId":"gen-1774493153-mGH1hEgmbQWBZJteHWr7"}}
